# Handled Home — Provider BYOC + Provider Onboarding UX Flows (PRD Addendum)
**Scope:** Customer invite scripts + in-app provider pitch + end-to-end UX flows + state machine + acceptance criteria  
**Applies to:** California launch (v1), mobile-only provider onboarding  
**Goal:** Maximize qualified provider conversion + BYOC migration while protecting standards (SKUs/Levels/proof/no-side-payments) and keeping ops approval clean.

---

## 0) Executive Summary
This addendum defines:
1) **BYOC customer invite scripts** (SMS + email + in-person) that providers send to migrate customers
2) **In-app provider pitch pages** (copy blocks + structure) for “Good News!” opportunity banners
3) **Full UX flows** (when each flow appears, how they branch, and what happens next)
4) **Provider onboarding state machine** + decision logic + ops queue requirements
5) **Acceptance criteria** and instrumentation so Lovable can implement without ambiguity

---

# PART A — BYOC Customer Invite Scripts (Provider → Customer)

## A1) Core principles for customer-facing BYOC messaging
- The customer must feel **no downside**
- The relationship stays the same (“you keep me as your provider”)
- The benefits are tangible:
  - pay by card (no checks/cash)
  - receipts with photos/checklists
  - add services anytime (bundle & save)
- Avoid saying: “new network for my back office” as the main reason
  - That positions Handled Home as billing software instead of “Your home is handled”
- Avoid promising permanent pricing changes
  - Use: “transition rate” if needed, or don’t mention pricing at all unless asked

---

## A2) SMS Script (Best-performing default)
**Provider sends to existing customer**

> Hey [Customer First Name] — it’s [Provider Name].  
> I’ve upgraded to a new system called **Handled Home** so you can **pay by card**, get **visit receipts with photos**, and easily manage your service.  
> **Nothing changes with our service** — I’m still your provider.  
>  
> Here’s your link to activate: [Invite Link]  
>  
> Once you’re in, you’ll also see other optional services available in your area (bundle & save), but your current service stays the same.

**If customer asks “Why?”**
> Mostly to make it easier for you (card payments + receipts) and to reduce admin time so I can stay more consistent on schedule.

