# PART C — Provider Onboarding UX Flows (PRD)

## C1) Provider Entry Flow (Role + zone + category)
**Trigger:** Provider installs app and selects “I’m a Provider”  
**Steps:**
1) Provider selects categories
2) Provider enters ZIP(s) (home base + service zips)
3) App resolves ZIP → zone and checks zone/category state
4) App shows opportunity banner(s) (one primary, plus secondary if multiple categories)
5) Provider taps Apply

**UX rule:** Do not show “generic provider signup” without referencing their zone/category opportunity.

---

## C2) Provider Application Flow (Wizard)
**Trigger:** Provider taps Apply Now  
**Wizard stages:**
1) Pitch page (benefits + how it works)
2) Provider profile (identity + business)
3) Services & availability
4) BYOC intake (optional but encouraged)
5) Compliance (category/state driven)
6) Standards + clause-by-clause acceptance
7) Payout setup (Stripe)
8) Review & submit

**Save-as-you-go:** Provider can exit and resume (application status = DRAFT).

---

## C3) Post-Submit Flow (Under Review)
**Trigger:** Provider submits application  
**State:** UNDER_REVIEW  
**Provider sees:**
- “Application submitted”
- checklist showing what’s pending:
  - “Ops review”
  - “Document verification” (if needed)
- optional: “Invite BYOC customers after approval” (disabled until approved)

**Provider can:** edit non-locked fields and upload missing docs.

---

## C4) Approval Flow (Approved / Approved with conditions)
**Trigger:** Ops approves  
**Provider sees (approved):**
- Welcome screen
- Setup checklist:
  1) Confirm availability
  2) Complete a “test job” walkthrough (optional)
  3) Set home base (if missing)
  4) BYOC invite tools (now unlocked)
- “You’re eligible for Founding Partner benefits in [ZONE]” (if applicable)

**Approved with conditions:**
- Show condition (e.g., “Courtesy upgrades disabled until 10 jobs”)
- Show exact next step to remove condition

---

## C5) Waitlist Flow (Waitlisted)
**Trigger:** zone/category is WAITLIST or ops sets WAITLIST  
**Provider sees:**
- “You’re on the waitlist for [ZONE] / [CATEGORY]”
- ability to update profile and docs
- “We’ll notify you when openings appear”

**Ops benefit:** keep pipeline warm without opening capacity.

---

## C6) Reject Flow (Rejected)
**Provider sees:**
- “Not approved at this time”
- reason template (missing license/insurance, outside zone, category full, quality mismatch)
- what to do next (reapply after uploading docs, join waitlist, etc.)

