# PART D — BYOC UX Flows (Provider-side + Customer-side)

## D1) Provider BYOC Center (after approval)
**Location:** Provider app → Growth/Customers → “Bring Your Customers (BYOC)”  
**Modules:**
1) “How BYOC works” (short)
2) Incentives summary (what they earn and when)
3) Invite tools:
   - Copy SMS script button
   - Copy email script button
   - Share invite link button
4) Track invites:
   - Sent
   - Activated
   - Retained 30/60/90 (if you implement bonuses)
5) Compliance note:
   - “Do not promise permanent pricing. Transition credits may apply.”

---

## D2) Provider chooses a BYOC service mapping (critical)
If providers are required to map customers to SKUs+Levels:
- Provider chooses category → chooses SKU + Level defaults
- System can offer defaults based on typical customers
- Provider can optionally choose a “Migration credit” policy preset (if you implement it)
- Provider then generates invite link(s)

**v1 simplification (recommended):**
- Providers do not select individual customer mappings at first
- They select category-level mapping defaults:
  - “For my pool customers, use Pool Service Level 2, weekly”
- Customer confirms details when activating
- Ops can review exceptions later

This reduces provider friction dramatically.

---

## D3) Customer Activation Flow (from invite link)
**Trigger:** Customer clicks provider invite link  
**Flow:**
1) Install app if needed → open deep link
2) “Your provider [Name] is now using Handled Home” (trust)
3) “Nothing changes — you keep your provider” (reassurance)
4) Confirm property address
5) Confirm service summary:
   - SKU + Level + cadence
   - “What’s included” bullet list
6) Add payment method
7) Confirm activation
8) Success:
   - “You’re set. Your home is handled.”
   - (Optional) show 2–4 tailored services available to bundle (from 3B signals)

**Important:** Do not overwhelm with upsells during activation. Earn trust first.

---

## D4) Post-activation: First receipt as hook
After the first fulfilled job:
- Customer receives Handled Receipt
- Receipt shows proof and makes the platform feel premium
- Only then show 1–2 tasteful “bundle next” suggestions

