# PART F — Acceptance Criteria (Lovable-ready)

## F1) Provider onboarding
- Provider can select categories and ZIPs and see the correct opportunity banner.
- Provider can start application, exit, and resume (DRAFT persists).
- Provider must accept all required clauses (one tap each) before submit.
- Provider can upload compliance docs (COI/license proof) when required by category.
- Provider can submit application and see status updates.
- Ops can approve/waitlist/reject, and provider sees the correct outcome state.

## F2) BYOC center
- Approved provider can access BYOC Center.
- Provider can copy SMS/email scripts and share invite link.
- Provider sees a list of invite statuses (sent/activated).
- Incentive logic can be stubbed as “coming soon” but tracking must exist.

## F3) Customer activation via invite link
- Invite deep link loads correct “provider migration” activation flow.
- Customer confirms property, payment, service summary, and activates successfully.
- Activated service is mapped to SKU + Level.
- Customer sees minimal friction (no heavy upsell during activation).

