# PART H — Opinionated Sequencing (to keep UX clean)
1) Provider sees opportunity message immediately after ZIP/category selection (don’t bury it)
2) Provider onboarding begins with benefits + standards preview (sets expectations)
3) BYOC tools unlock only after approval (prevents spam)
4) Customer activation flow prioritizes reassurance + payment + confirmation
5) Upsells wait until the first receipt (trust moment)

---

# PART I — Build Notes (to keep implementation simple)
- Keep compliance requirements category-driven via a config table:
  - requires_license (bool)
  - requires_coi (bool)
  - requires_background_check (bool)
  - min_insurance_amount (number)
- Use Stripe Connect for payouts + W-9 to avoid storing sensitive data.
- Keep “non-circumvention” clause narrow in CA; enforce platform integrity through:
  - no side payments
  - proof requirements
  - provider removal
